00:05:02.070 --> 00:05:04.600
And obviously, from a consumer
point of view, that wasn't the

00:05:04.600 --> 00:05:05.400
best experience.

00:05:05.400 --> 00:05:09.030
So we improved the experience a
lot by creating something we

00:05:09.030 --> 00:05:11.650
call the product page, which
is, this particular camera,

00:05:11.650 --> 00:05:15.150
Canon Power Shot, is sold
by multiple retailers.

00:05:15.150 --> 00:05:19.420
In fact, 158 retailers, but
it's is the same product.

00:05:19.420 --> 00:05:22.520
There's no point showing that
image 158 times, or the

00:05:22.520 --> 00:05:24.350
description, or the ratings
and reviews.

00:05:24.350 --> 00:05:27.130
Because no matter whom you buy
this product from, the product

00:05:27.130 --> 00:05:28.100
remains the same.

00:05:28.100 --> 00:05:31.820
So we created this canonical
catalog pages for the products

00:05:31.820 --> 00:05:35.410
so that, as a consumer, as you
are typing in a query, we show

00:05:35.410 --> 00:05:36.250
you this product page.

00:05:36.250 --> 00:05:38.740
You can look at all the
information about the product

00:05:38.740 --> 00:05:41.840
and then, at the bottom grid,
you see all the retailers.

00:05:41.840 --> 00:05:43.800
We still show you the retailers
ratings, because

00:05:43.800 --> 00:05:44.950
that's equally important.

00:05:44.950 --> 00:05:47.690
Once you know that this is the
