00:06:50.670 --> 00:06:53.930
with a mobile device.

00:06:53.930 --> 00:06:57.430
This is something which is my
personal favorite, which is

00:06:57.430 --> 00:06:59.350
mobile meets local.

00:06:59.350 --> 00:07:02.600
We went from desktop-based
shopping, to a canonical

00:07:02.600 --> 00:07:05.800
product, to mobile, and then
this is the ultimate nirvana

00:07:05.800 --> 00:07:09.010
where now, I can not only search
that product, but it

00:07:09.010 --> 00:07:12.330
tells me precisely that this
item is available on these

00:07:12.330 --> 00:07:13.940
stores near me.

00:07:13.940 --> 00:07:16.630
And in fact, we get-- and this
is why the API is important--

00:07:16.630 --> 00:07:20.510
we get this real time inventory
feed from all these

00:07:20.510 --> 00:07:24.160
retailers so we can precisely
tell you whether this item is

00:07:24.160 --> 00:07:26.950
on the shelves at that
store or not.

00:07:26.950 --> 00:07:30.420
Because the opposite of it is,
you find a product, you like

00:07:30.420 --> 00:07:33.170
it, you drive to a store,
and guess what?

00:07:33.170 --> 00:07:34.355
That item is not available.

00:07:34.355 --> 00:07:36.980
And I call that phenomenon
anticipointment.

00:07:36.980 --> 00:07:39.920
I kind of felt this anticipation
like, I got the

00:07:39.920 --> 00:07:40.900
product, I want to buy it.

00:07:40.900 --> 00:07:41.970
You walk into the store.

00:07:41.970 --> 00:07:43.720
It's not there and you
get disappointed.

00:07:43.720 --> 00:07:45.940
We wanted to make sure we
avoid that phenomenon of

00:07:45.940 --> 00:07:50.210
anticipointment, and wow the
users by giving them this

00:07:50.210 --> 00:07:52.770
perfect information and giving
them this assurance that this

00:07:52.770 --> 00:07:57.090
item is actually on the shelf
right now in a store near you.

00:07:57.090 --> 00:07:59.450
And then last, but not the
least, you can obviously click

00:07:59.450 --> 00:08:02.150
on Get Directions and it will
guide you to that store.

00:08:02.150 --> 00:08:03.360
What can be better than that?

00:08:03.360 --> 00:08:05.560
And this is really changing how

00:08:05.560 --> 00:08:06.850
people think about shopping.

00:08:06.850 --> 00:08:09.050
Because back in the days,
there was this clear

00:08:09.050 --> 00:08:12.090
distinction between what was
online shopping and what was

00:08:12.090 --> 00:08:13.000
shopping at the store.

00:08:13.000 --> 00:08:15.810
The reality is that there
is no such distinction.

00:08:15.810 --> 00:08:16.950
These worlds are merging.

00:08:16.950 --> 00:08:20.270
A lot of times users will walk
into the store, but complete

00:08:20.270 --> 00:08:22.000
the transaction in
the online world.

00:08:22.000 --> 00:08:24.920
Or vice versa, which is a more
common scenario, they will

00:08:24.920 --> 00:08:28.090
start their research online but
finish their transaction

00:08:28.090 --> 00:08:29.150
at a physical store.

00:08:29.150 --> 00:08:31.150
And there are various reasons
why they do so.

00:08:31.150 --> 00:08:34.990
And as a retailer, as an
e-commerce website owner, you

00:08:34.990 --> 00:08:37.090
want to make sure that you give
the best choice to the

00:08:37.090 --> 00:08:39.130
consumer, and let them
pick what's most

00:08:39.130 --> 00:08:39.842
convenient for them.

00:08:39.842 --> 00:08:42.620
And this kind of local shopping
and mobile blends

00:08:42.620 --> 00:08:45.840
these two worlds perfectly.

00:08:45.840 --> 00:08:51.030
So what are Google's shopping
APIs and how does it relate to

00:08:51.030 --> 00:08:54.910
all the innovations that I
showed you on google.com?

00:08:54.910 --> 00:08:57.290
So the shopping APIs
are essentially

00:08:57.290 --> 00:08:59.110
divided into two segments.

00:08:59.110 --> 00:09:01.300
So this is kind of my style
of drawing a simple

00:09:01.300 --> 00:09:02.520
architectural diagram.

00:09:02.520 --> 00:09:05.810
So bear with me as I try to
walk you through very bare

00:09:05.810 --> 00:09:07.090
bones components here.

00:09:07.090 --> 00:09:09.330
But if you look at the heart
of it, we have something

00:09:09.330 --> 00:09:13.680
called Google Merchant Center,
which is our webmaster kind of

00:09:13.680 --> 00:09:16.200
tools for uploading
data to Google.

00:09:16.200 --> 00:09:20.260
How many people are aware of
Google Merchant Center?

00:09:20.260 --> 00:09:21.430
OK, so this is pretty good.

00:09:21.430 --> 00:09:23.760
It looks like at least
half of the audience.

00:09:23.760 --> 00:09:25.750
But for those of you who are
not developers, Google

00:09:25.750 --> 00:09:29.260
Merchant Center is our simple
dashboard where you, as a

00:09:29.260 --> 00:09:31.650
developer, or if you're working
for a retailer, can

00:09:31.650 --> 00:09:34.780
interact with it to upload the
items that you but sell on

00:09:34.780 --> 00:09:37.220
your website or in a physical
store near you.

00:09:37.220 --> 00:09:39.560
And what you see at the bottom
of this slide is

00:09:39.560 --> 00:09:40.780
two different avenues.

00:09:40.780 --> 00:09:43.970
So you can either upload
this data, what we call

00:09:43.970 --> 00:09:44.790
Product Data Feed.

00:09:44.790 --> 00:09:48.730
These are simple XML or Excel
files, and you can simply go

00:09:48.730 --> 00:09:50.930
to the Merchant Center and
click File Upload,

00:09:50.930 --> 00:09:52.435
and upload that file.

00:09:52.435 --> 00:09:54.460
Or you can use this new
API, which is the

00:09:54.460 --> 00:09:56.190
Content API for shopping.

00:09:56.190 --> 00:09:59.900
This API has much more tighter
libraries, that's much more

00:09:59.900 --> 00:10:03.230
easier for a developer to
program against them and

00:10:03.230 --> 00:10:05.150
integrate back into
your system.

00:10:05.150 --> 00:10:07.550
Also the Content API
allows you to do

00:10:07.550 --> 00:10:08.750
more incremental updates.

00:10:08.750 --> 00:10:12.050
So one of the most common
requirements we see is to

00:10:12.050 --> 00:10:14.180
update price and inventory,
right?

00:10:14.180 --> 00:10:16.090
During the day, a retailer
changes its

00:10:16.090 --> 00:10:18.370
price multiple times.

00:10:18.370 --> 00:10:22.350
If you change your price from
$60 to $49, you want to make

00:10:22.350 --> 00:10:24.780
sure that that price is updated
within minutes.

00:10:24.780 --> 00:10:27.820
So the Content API allows you to
do that, as well as, if you

00:10:27.820 --> 00:10:30.990
run out of the stock with some
item, you can do so without

00:10:30.990 --> 00:10:32.470
uploading your entire
inventory.

00:10:32.470 --> 00:10:35.730
We can make those fine grained
incremental updates.

00:10:35.730 --> 00:10:38.370
So we're going to talk a lot
about Content API today.

00:10:38.370 --> 00:10:41.070
But at this point, I just wanted
to give you a high

00:10:41.070 --> 00:10:41.980
level overview.

00:10:41.980 --> 00:10:45.200
And then, on the client site,
obviously, I showed you a lot

00:10:45.200 --> 00:10:47.940
of innovations on google.com,
which is the box Google

00:10:47.940 --> 00:10:48.540
Shopping represents.

00:10:48.540 --> 00:10:51.870
But what's more interesting,
you can take those same

00:10:51.870 --> 00:10:55.600
innovations and power search on
