00:12:58.750 --> 00:13:02.870
So they're HTTP-based APIs, in
the same way that your web

00:13:02.870 --> 00:13:03.780
browser is.

00:13:03.780 --> 00:13:06.760
And we have a resource and
that resource has a URI

00:13:06.760 --> 00:13:08.460
associated with it.

00:13:08.460 --> 00:13:12.330
We make a request that's
identical to a web request.

00:13:12.330 --> 00:13:16.840
That can be any one of the verbs
that we have, get, post,

00:13:16.840 --> 00:13:18.130
put, delete.

00:13:18.130 --> 00:13:20.040
There are others, but those are
the important ones we'll

00:13:20.040 --> 00:13:21.800
be looking at today.

00:13:21.800 --> 00:13:24.330
And we get a response back, and
that response can contain

00:13:24.330 --> 00:13:28.520
the data in any of the data
formats, such as JSON and XML,

00:13:28.520 --> 00:13:30.590
which are the ones were going
to be using today.

00:13:30.590 --> 00:13:33.660
So if you're familiar with
RESTful APIs, if you've heard

00:13:33.660 --> 00:13:36.470
of the concept REST, this is
all going to be a bit more

00:13:36.470 --> 00:13:37.210
obvious for you.

00:13:37.210 --> 00:13:39.790
But essentially, we have
resources, we make requests,

00:13:39.790 --> 00:13:43.420
and we get responses back.

00:13:43.420 --> 00:13:45.000
What is the data format like?

00:13:45.000 --> 00:13:47.170
Well, I said it was either
XML or JSON.

00:13:47.170 --> 00:13:49.280
And you do have a choice
with this API whether

00:13:49.280 --> 00:13:51.560
you use XML or JSON.

00:13:51.560 --> 00:13:55.790
The default format is XML, for
this API and that really suits

00:13:55.790 --> 00:13:57.440
the more enterprisey feel.

00:13:57.440 --> 00:14:00.070
Enterprises like using XML.

00:14:00.070 --> 00:14:04.010
It's built on GData and the Atom
Syndication Format, so

00:14:04.010 --> 00:14:07.450
that we have a feed, corresponds
to a list of

00:14:07.450 --> 00:14:11.130
products, and an Atom
entry corresponds to

00:14:11.130 --> 00:14:12.360
an individual product.

00:14:12.360 --> 00:14:15.000
And inside there, we have the
various products attributes.

00:14:18.060 --> 00:14:20.710
You can see there the title,
the Atom title.

00:14:20.710 --> 00:14:22.820
And this is for an army knife,
a Swiss Army knife.

00:14:22.820 --> 00:14:25.590
I live in Zurich so we
know our knives.

00:14:25.590 --> 00:14:27.740
And you can repeat some elements
in that, so that's a

00:14:27.740 --> 00:14:29.800
very high overview of that.

00:14:29.800 --> 00:14:33.020
And we'll look at the individual
data model.

00:14:33.020 --> 00:14:37.910
So each product we have, each
product you give us, you send

00:14:37.910 --> 00:14:41.430
to us, is uniquely identified
by those four components you

00:14:41.430 --> 00:14:43.920
see there: the channel by
which you're selling

00:14:43.920 --> 00:14:45.890
it, which is online.

00:14:45.890 --> 00:14:49.580
EN there, which is the language,
the country, U.S.

00:14:49.580 --> 00:14:53.040
and your SKU, your individual
code for that.

00:14:53.040 --> 00:14:56.620
So those four components are
stuck together to make the

00:14:56.620 --> 00:14:58.370
unique ID for the product.

00:14:58.370 --> 00:15:00.290
That's worth knowing.

00:15:00.290 --> 00:15:00.790
Why?

00:15:00.790 --> 00:15:03.400
Because if you upload the same
product for a different

00:15:03.400 --> 00:15:06.590
country, or the same product
with a different language,

00:15:06.590 --> 00:15:10.110
that's regarded by our system
as a different product.

00:15:10.110 --> 00:15:12.640
So inside that product, we
have various attributes.

00:15:12.640 --> 00:15:15.500
I've only got the title
one up there.

00:15:15.500 --> 00:15:18.590
And each product can belong
to a number of product

00:15:18.590 --> 00:15:19.270
categories.

00:15:19.270 --> 00:15:22.160
And we provide a taxonomy
for that that is fairly

00:15:22.160 --> 00:15:25.980
comprehensive, so it should
cover all your product needs.

00:15:25.980 --> 00:15:29.730
As you'll see, we recommend
you use all of these.

00:15:29.730 --> 00:15:31.530
The schema itself.

00:15:31.530 --> 00:15:34.080
We have created a new namespace,
a couple of

00:15:34.080 --> 00:15:37.680
namespaces to add on to the Atom
namespace to extend what

00:15:37.680 --> 00:15:38.240
you can see.

00:15:38.240 --> 00:15:40.410
The title is the
product title.

00:15:40.410 --> 00:15:43.170
The content is the product
description.

00:15:43.170 --> 00:15:45.680
The link is the link to
the product page.

00:15:45.680 --> 00:15:47.090
That's really important.

00:15:47.090 --> 00:15:49.410
We don't host your product
information.

00:15:49.410 --> 00:15:52.030
We require a link from you--

00:15:52.030 --> 00:15:53.190
a URL--

00:15:53.190 --> 00:15:55.020
to a place where people can see

00:15:55.020 --> 00:15:56.340
information about that product.

00:15:56.340 --> 00:15:58.450
Now typically, you know what
I'm talking about.

00:15:58.450 --> 00:16:00.710
There's an image there, there's
the price there, you

00:16:00.710 --> 00:16:03.390
can click, Add to Cart, and
some product information.

00:16:03.390 --> 00:16:05.720
But we really require that.

00:16:05.720 --> 00:16:08.190
And then there are
some individual

00:16:08.190 --> 00:16:09.830
elements for our API.

00:16:09.830 --> 00:16:12.380
So the target country, that
comprises part of

00:16:12.380 --> 00:16:14.130
the ID that I said.

00:16:14.130 --> 00:16:16.330
The content language,
that's the language

00:16:16.330 --> 00:16:17.920
of the content element.

00:16:17.920 --> 00:16:21.250
The condition, we do require you
to tell us the condition

00:16:21.250 --> 00:16:24.110
of the product, new, used,
or refurbished.

00:16:24.110 --> 00:16:27.390
Information about the price,
including currency, and some

00:16:27.390 --> 00:16:29.410
images, or one or more images.

00:16:29.410 --> 00:16:32.830
We do ask for one high quality
image, at least. So those are

00:16:32.830 --> 00:16:34.570
the important required
elements.

00:16:34.570 --> 00:16:38.000
There are many more, 30 or 40,
and they're well documented.

00:16:38.000 --> 00:16:41.230
You can see the links
afterward.

00:16:41.230 --> 00:16:41.460
Right.

00:16:41.460 --> 00:16:44.760
Before I show the actual request
and response, I want

00:16:44.760 --> 00:16:47.685
to give you some tips for
getting your products higher

00:16:47.685 --> 00:16:50.450
in the ranking, OK?

00:16:50.450 --> 00:16:53.700
This is really important and
they're all really, really

00:16:53.700 --> 00:16:54.420
common sense.

00:16:54.420 --> 00:16:56.250
So you're saying, oh, but
that's common sense.

00:16:56.250 --> 00:16:59.240
But actually, if you do all of
them, it will significantly

00:16:59.240 --> 00:17:00.760
improve your rankings.

00:17:00.760 --> 00:17:05.130
So firstly, fill out as many
fields as you can.

00:17:05.130 --> 00:17:08.400
Our user of this product, Google
Shopping, google.com,

00:17:08.400 --> 00:17:10.619
is the person trying
to find something.

00:17:10.619 --> 00:17:13.710
So it's me trying to buy a
digital camera, or it's you

00:17:13.710 --> 00:17:16.800
trying to buy something that
you want, a bicycle.

00:17:16.800 --> 00:17:19.829
Those are the users and we're
really keen, at Google, to

00:17:19.829 --> 00:17:22.220
give users exactly what
they're looking

00:17:22.220 --> 00:17:23.210
for, the best data.

00:17:23.210 --> 00:17:26.050
And we can give them that data
if you give it to us.

00:17:26.050 --> 00:17:28.960
So firstly, fill out as many
fields as you can.

00:17:28.960 --> 00:17:32.820
Secondly, use good
quality images.

00:17:32.820 --> 00:17:34.270
People love looking at stuff.

00:17:34.270 --> 00:17:36.400
We all love looking at stuff,
and if you can see something,

00:17:36.400 --> 00:17:36.990
you're going to buy it.

00:17:36.990 --> 00:17:41.620
That's a really, really strong
motivator to actually buy it.

00:17:41.620 --> 00:17:44.730
We do check that the images you
give us do exist. We do

00:17:44.730 --> 00:17:47.970
check that the product pages do
exist. We do check that the

00:17:47.970 --> 00:17:51.720
prices on the product page is
accurate to the information

00:17:51.720 --> 00:17:52.710
that you sent us.

00:17:52.710 --> 00:17:56.910
And if there are discrepancies
with those, that can adversely

00:17:56.910 --> 00:17:59.680
affect your rankings.

00:17:59.680 --> 00:18:01.170
Product identifiers.

00:18:01.170 --> 00:18:03.490
I very briefly mention
this here.

00:18:03.490 --> 00:18:07.440
Books have ISBN numbers,
products have UPC codes, and

00:18:07.440 --> 00:18:11.530
more recently there is
a g10 Code that is

00:18:11.530 --> 00:18:12.440
used by both of them.

00:18:12.440 --> 00:18:14.550
It's a generalization
of both of them.

00:18:14.550 --> 00:18:18.540
Now if you give us these
identifiers, then we can

00:18:18.540 --> 00:18:23.080
accurately place your products
on one of those catalog pages.

00:18:23.080 --> 00:18:26.160
So we know that the digital
camera is the exact same

00:18:26.160 --> 00:18:29.880
digital camera, and that will
put you in that catalog page.

00:18:29.880 --> 00:18:34.990
And also, it's very good for
your rankings as well.

00:18:34.990 --> 00:18:35.920
Product categories.

00:18:35.920 --> 00:18:37.410
People do like to search
by category.

00:18:37.410 --> 00:18:40.400
They do like to browse
products by category.

00:18:40.400 --> 00:18:42.880
And if you use our taxonomy,
then we can provide the

00:18:42.880 --> 00:18:44.980
results when people are
looking for them.

00:18:44.980 --> 00:18:47.330
Again, it's all about the users,
all about the person

00:18:47.330 --> 00:18:47.510
who's looking.

00:18:47.510 --> 00:18:49.920
So if you give us the
information, then we can index

00:18:49.920 --> 00:18:51.330
it accurately.

00:18:51.330 --> 00:18:52.670
Good titles and good
descriptions.

00:18:52.670 --> 00:18:54.000
This is my favorite one.

00:18:54.000 --> 00:18:57.070
Don't write your titles
in all capitals.

00:18:57.070 --> 00:18:58.360
Use good punctuation.

00:18:58.360 --> 00:18:59.750
Ensure they're well spelled.

00:18:59.750 --> 00:19:02.750
We do check all of these things,
and again, we want to

00:19:02.750 --> 00:19:04.060
give the user a good
experience.

00:19:04.060 --> 00:19:07.990
So we don't want to show them
all capitals, so we won't.

00:19:07.990 --> 00:19:10.340
And the last one is
more general.

00:19:10.340 --> 00:19:14.440
Include information about
tax and shipping.

00:19:14.440 --> 00:19:15.550
I've had the same experience.

00:19:15.550 --> 00:19:17.610
If I don't know how much tax I'm
going to pay on a product,

00:19:17.610 --> 00:19:19.750
I just won't even consider
buying from that site.

00:19:19.750 --> 00:19:21.650
If I don't know how much it's
going to cost to get it sent

00:19:21.650 --> 00:19:23.220
to me, I won't even consider.

00:19:23.220 --> 00:19:24.390
And it's so important.

00:19:24.390 --> 00:19:27.450
If you noticed, on Nitin's
demonstration, with all the

00:19:27.450 --> 00:19:30.190
merchants, alongside reviews,
it had tax and shipping

00:19:30.190 --> 00:19:30.680
information.

00:19:30.680 --> 00:19:33.570
It's that important that we
want to show that to users

00:19:33.570 --> 00:19:36.450
immediately, because it
can affect where they

00:19:36.450 --> 00:19:37.850
decide to buy from.

00:19:37.850 --> 00:19:39.440
So those are my tips.

00:19:39.440 --> 00:19:41.220
If you want to discuss
