00:20:02.610 --> 00:20:05.330
For example, if you want to
insert a product that's not

00:20:05.330 --> 00:20:08.100
specific to a single product,
and so we would use this

00:20:08.100 --> 00:20:11.130
endpoint, or to retrieve a list
of all your products.

00:20:11.130 --> 00:20:15.380
Now that's made up of a few
bits, the root URI.

00:20:15.380 --> 00:20:17.860
That's the URI of the API.

00:20:17.860 --> 00:20:21.060
Then the merchant ID is only
one, two, three, four, five,

00:20:21.060 --> 00:20:23.300
and all merchants who have
signed up for the Merchant

00:20:23.300 --> 00:20:25.170
Center have an ID.

00:20:25.170 --> 00:20:27.510
The path and then
the projection.

00:20:27.510 --> 00:20:29.160
I won't be talking about
the projection.

00:20:29.160 --> 00:20:32.020
It's an advanced option
on how we return some

00:20:32.020 --> 00:20:34.510
extended parts of XML.

00:20:34.510 --> 00:20:36.520
You can read about that, and
again, that's something I can

00:20:36.520 --> 00:20:38.720
talk to you about individually
if you're interested.

00:20:38.720 --> 00:20:40.070
So that's the product
endpoint.

00:20:40.070 --> 00:20:43.950
That's where we send any request
which is general for

00:20:43.950 --> 00:20:45.640
the merchant.

00:20:45.640 --> 00:20:48.390
The second endpoint is a
specific endpoint for every

00:20:48.390 --> 00:20:49.740
single product.

00:20:49.740 --> 00:20:55.130
It's identical up until the
point where we add on the end,

00:20:55.130 --> 00:20:58.130
the four part product ID that
I spoke about earlier.

00:20:58.130 --> 00:21:00.840
So you can see, it's joined
by [? curl lines ?]

