00:30:45.860 --> 00:30:48.840
of business, if you're in an
aggregator-type business.

00:30:48.840 --> 00:30:50.090
Think of the marketplaces.

00:30:52.700 --> 00:30:56.340
Just a little example of when,
just to put it into context.

00:30:56.340 --> 00:30:59.110
Now this is the simplest flow
you can have. So you have an

00:30:59.110 --> 00:31:00.190
ERP system.

00:31:00.190 --> 00:31:03.590
If you're a normal retailer,
you have an ERP system, but

00:31:03.590 --> 00:31:06.600
when something changes, you send
a notification to your

00:31:06.600 --> 00:31:09.830
module that will handle this,
and that will make a single

00:31:09.830 --> 00:31:12.330
call to the Content
API for Shopping.

00:31:12.330 --> 00:31:15.380
You write it once and you just
leave it forever, and for the

00:31:15.380 --> 00:31:18.510
rest of time, your products
will be accurate in Google

00:31:18.510 --> 00:31:20.540
Product Search, all the
time, up to date.

00:31:20.540 --> 00:31:22.030
People can find them
and people will

00:31:22.030 --> 00:31:23.700
be able to buy them.

00:31:23.700 --> 00:31:27.630
So the Content API for Shopping,
an HTTP-based API

00:31:27.630 --> 00:31:30.480
based on Atom and GData
by default.

00:31:30.480 --> 00:31:33.920
Use it to manage your product
data for Google Product Search

00:31:33.920 --> 00:31:37.520
and Google Shopping, easy to
manage data feeds for yourself

00:31:37.520 --> 00:31:40.180
or third parties, and you
can manage subaccounts.

00:31:40.180 --> 00:31:41.300
So that's that.

